== Production and sales ==
[[File:Receiving Tesla Model X (VIN 2).jpg|thumb|upright=0.9|[[Elon Musk]] delivering one of the first six Model X (VIN 0002) Founders Series models to Tesla board member [[Steve Jurvetson]]]]
Tesla started taking reservations for the Model X in February 2012 without announcing prices.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hybridcars.com/tesla-model-x-reservations-hit-500-24-hours-38538/|title=Tesla Model X Reservations Hit 500 in 24 Hours|website=HybridCars.com}}</ref> The standard Model X required a {{USD|5,000}} deposit, while the limited time production Signature model required a {{USD|40,000}} deposit in 2013.<ref name=NYT032013>{{cite news|url= http://wheels.blogs.nytimes.com/2013/03/12/tesla-model-x-production-wont-start-until-late-2014/?ref=automobiles |title=Tesla Model X Production Won't Start Until Late 2014|author=Bradley Berman|newspaper=[[The New York Times]]|date=March 12, 2013 |access-date=March 12, 2013}}</ref> More than 20,000 Model Xs had been reserved by September 2014.<ref>{{cite web|url= http://green.autoblog.com/2014/09/11/tesla-model-x-reservations-20000-strong-and-counting/ |title=Tesla Model X reservations 20,000 strong and counting|author=Danny King|website=Autoblog}}</ref> In August 2015, user groups estimated around 30,000 Model X [[pre-order]]s had been received, compared to 12,000 for the Model S.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.businessfinancenews.com/23587-tesla-motors-inc-model-x-preorders-cross-30000-units/|title=Tesla Motors Inc (TSLA) Model X Pre-Orders Cross 30,000 Units|website=businessfinancenews.com|quote=The table formed by TMC reveals that the electric vehicle (EV) company has received 30,027 Model X reservations worldwide. – The sedan was able to receive only 12,000 pre-orders ahead of its launch.|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150926151030/http://www.businessfinancenews.com/23587-tesla-motors-inc-model-x-preorders-cross-30000-units/|archive-date=September 26, 2015|df=mdy-all}}</ref>

The first six Founders Series models were delivered at a market launch event in the Fremont factory on September 29, 2015.<ref name=ModelXfirst>{{cite web|url= http://www.greencarcongress.com/2015/09/20140930-modelx.html |title=Tesla CEO Musk launches Model X electric SUV: "safest SUV ever"|author=Mike Millikin|publisher=Green Car Congress|date=September 30, 2015|access-date=October 3, 2015}}</ref> The first Signature edition was delivered on December 18, 2015.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.teslamotorsclub.com/showthread.php/59174-Signature-1-delivered-today |date=December 18, 2015 |access-date=December 19, 2015 |title=Signature #1 delivered today |website=Tesla Motors Club}}</ref> Pricing for the limited edition Signature version of the Model X varies between {{USD|132,000}} and {{USD|144,000}},<ref name=cnbc20150903>{{cite news|url= https://www.cnbc.com/2015/09/03/tesla-signature-series-model-x-to-begin-delivery-september-29.html |title=Tesla Signature series Model X to begin delivery September 29|agency=[[Reuters]] |publisher=CNBC |date=September 3, 2015 |access-date=September 4, 2015}}</ref>  while the standard production version of the Model X will be priced at {{USD|5,000}}<!-- These are not yet being sold. --> more than a comparably equipped AWD Model S that is priced at {{USD|75,000}} for the base Model 70D.<ref>{{cite web|title = Tesla's long-delayed Model X SUV hits the road as sales of luxury SUVs are booming|url = https://www.usnews.com/news/business/articles/2015/09/29/teslas-first-suv-the-model-x-is-finally-hitting-the-road |access-date = September 30, 2015}}</ref>

After the first quarter of 2016 all Tesla Model X deliveries had gone to US customers. Nevertheless, in January 2016 a Tesla car other than the Model S was registered in Germany and a Tesla Model X was sighted driving there with a license plate from [[Ingolstadt]]. Since the [[Audi]] headquarters are located in Ingolstadt, this led to speculation that Audi has acquired a Tesla Model X as part of its effort to develop its own battery-electric SUV.<ref>{{cite news|url= http://teslamag.de/news/erstes-tesla-model-x-deutschland-6849 |title= Erstes Tesla Model X in Deutschland gesichtet |website= teslamag.de |date= January 31, 2016 |access-date= April 10, 2016 |trans-title= First Tesla Model X sighted in Germany |language=de}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url= http://teslamag.de/news/tesla-fahrzeugzulassungen-in-deutschland-fuer-januar-2016-6911 |title= Tesla: Fahrzeugzulassungen in Deutschland für Januar 2016 |website= teslamag.de |date= February 5, 2016 |access-date= April 10, 2016 |trans-title= Tesla: Vehicle registrations in Germany for January 2016 |language=de}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url= https://electrek.co/2016/04/19/audi-charge-tesla-model-x-reverse-engineering/ |title=Audi is reverse-engineering/benchmarking a Tesla Model X but doesn't know how to charge it|first=Fred |last=Lambert|date= April 19, 2016 |website=Electrek |access-date=December 26, 2016 }}</ref>

Tesla produced 507 Model X in the fourth quarter of 2015, of which 206 were delivered to customers.<ref name=Tesla4Q2015>{{cite web| url= http://files.shareholder.com/downloads/ABEA-4CW8X0/456867397x0x874449/945B9CF5-86DA-4C35-B03C-4892824F058D/Q4_15_Tesla_Update_Letter.pdf | title=Tesla Fourth Quarter & Full Year 2015 Update | author= Tesla Motors|publisher=Tesla Motors|date=February 10, 2016|access-date=August 4, 2016}} ''A total of 17,478 units were delivered globally during the fourth quarter of 2015, including 206 Model X vehicles.  Model S sales in the United States totaled 16,689 units in 2014 and 25,202 in 2015.''</ref> Model X sales totaled 2,400 units during the first quarter of 2016.<ref name=Tesla1Q2016>{{cite press release |url= http://www.marketwired.com/press-release/tesla-delivers-14820-vehicles-in-q1-2016-on-track-for-full-year-delivery-guidance-nasdaq-tsla-2111728.htm | title=Tesla Delivers 14,820 Vehicles in Q1 2016; On Track for Full-Year Delivery Guidance |publisher=Market Wired |author=[[Tesla, Inc.]] |location=[[Palo Alto]] |date=April 4, 2016 |access-date=April 4, 2016}}</ref> According to Tesla Motors, deliveries were lower than expected because production was impacted by severe Model X supplier parts shortages in the first two months of 2016, and because Tesla had been too ambitious in wanting advanced features (committed "[[hubris]]").<ref name=Tesla1Q2016 /> The first Model X that didn't need corrections was made in April<!--29--> 2016.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.autoblog.com/2016/05/05/tesla-model-3-manufacturing-process/ |title=With Model 3, Tesla will approach manufacturing in a new way |first=Sebastion |last=Blanco |website=Autoblog |date=May 5, 2016 |access-date=July 25, 2016}}</ref>

